have to add visible property in IndividualSeriesOptions interface.

title: [react] Allow projects to use React declarations without the DOM lib dependency.
body:
React is used in some environments outside the browser, notably React Native.
For these kinds of projects, it is preferable for the TypeScript compiler to not include `--lib dom` since this brings it numerous global definitions that will not be available at runtime. To accommodate these use cases, the React declarations need to provide empty definitions of DOM, HTML, and SVG interfaces so that the declarations can compile. For projects that do include the full TypeScript DOM library, these empty interfaces will be merged with those provided by TypeScript.

See the discussion in React Native #19840.
